      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Ibn Fazzal, from Ibn Bukeyr, from Muhammad Bin Muslim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having disliked for the man to spend the night alone upon a roof, or upon a rood with no enclosure upon it, and the man and the woman with regards to it are at the same status’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "4. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn ‘Isa from ibn Faddal from ibn Bukayr from Muhammad ibn Muslim who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, disliked a man’s sleeping alone overnight on a flat roof without safety fencing wall around it; and that it is the same for both men and women.’” "
        ]
      }
